  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p>Reporting into the Assistant Operations Manager, you will be responsible for supporting sales order processing and fulfilment operations, coordinating deliveries, inventory and sales orders analysis/reporting.</p><p>The role plays a key part in ensuring order accuracy, inventory availability, and on-time delivery to support business growth and customer satisfaction.</p><p>Specifically, you will</p><ul><li>Liaise with Sales to understand demand requirements and provide purchase order analysis for confirmation of quantities.</li><li>Update orders in ERP system and place orders with the suppliers.</li><li>Liaise and follow up with suppliers on shipping arrangement as well as co-ordinate with freight forwarder and manage custom clearance.</li><li>Manage inventory accuracy by ensuring physical stock and system records are aligned, and investigate discrepancies where required.</li><li>Prepare and submit monthly reports to Management and Division Managers.</li><li>Coordinate the deployment and utilization of the Dispatch for delivery, support process improvement to enhance efficiency and undertake cost-benefit analysis.</li><li>Liaise and follow up with shipping service providers.</li></ul><p>Key Requirements</p><ul><li>Minimum diploma with 1-2 years of relevant work experience in logistics.</li><li>Fresh graduates are welcome to apply.</li><li>You should be proficient in Microsoft Dynamics.</li><li>Possess good interpersonal and communication skills and demonstrate ownership, initiative, and attention to detail in a fast-moving operations environment.</li><li>Having a growth mindset, customer focused and able to work independently as well as collaboratively in a\nteam are desired attributes.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
